TY  - JOUR
AU  - Allen, Franklin
AU  - Gale, Douglas
T1  - Optimal Security Design
PY  - 1988
Y1  - 1988/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/1.3.229
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 1
IS  - 3
SP  - 229
EP  - 263
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - How should new securities be designed? Traditional theories have little to say on this: the literature on capital structure and general equilibrium theories with incomplete markets takes the securities firms issue as exogenous. This article explicitly incorporates the transaction costs of issuing securities and develops a model in which the instruments that are traded are chosen optimally and the economy's market structure is endogenous. Among other things, it is shown that the firm's income stream should be split so that in every state all payoffs are allocated to the security held by the group that values it most.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/1.3.229
ER  - 



